                            <comment id="14095356" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 11:04:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12661430/12661430_d6703-1a.diff&quot; title=&quot;d6703-1a.diff attached to DERBY-6703&quot;&gt;d6703-1a.diff&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; makes the following changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;MergeNode.addColumn()&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use a different bind method for binding the ColumnReference. That method will raise an exception instead of silently returning null if the column is not in the from list.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove the handling of tableName being null (which is where the NPE happened). No longer needed since a no such column error will already have been raised in the cases where tableName previously could be null.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;MergeStatementTest&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add test case. There already was a test for invalid columns in the ON clause, but it didn&apos;t expose the problem because it used a qualified name. The new test case uses an unqualified name.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;FromList.bindColumnReference()&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mention the possibility of returning null in the javadoc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;ColumnReference.bindExpression()&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make return type more specific (ValueNode -&amp;gt; ColumnReference) to prevent the need for a cast in MergeNode.addColumn().&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;All regression tests ran cleanly with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
